-- Indian shares rise for fourth consecutive session
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Tue May 20, 2014 06:16AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 20 (Reuters) - Indian shares edged higher to a fourth consecutive session of gains on Tuesday as domestic-oriented stocks such as Sesa Sterlite rose on continued hopes that the incoming government would revive the economy, while IT stocks rebounded after recent sharp falls.

Sesa Sterlite Ltd <SESA.NS> provisionally surged 8 percent. Infosys <INFY.NS> unofficially rose 2.8 percent after falling 7.9 percent in the last two sessions, while Tata Consultancy Services <TCS.NS> gained 1.2 percent.